## Philips WiZ (Protocol Details)
The WiZ integration uses standard Python sockets communicating over the publicly known, local UDP JSON-RPC protocol (Port 38899). It does not include any proprietary SDKs, firmware blobs, or reverse-engineered cryptographic material.

## WLED (Protocol Details)
The WLED integration uses standard HTTP JSON requests and UDP DRGB (Port 21324) based on the public WLED API documentation.

## Windows Dynamic Lighting
Integrates with the Windows 11 Runtime (WinRT) `LampArray` API. Requires Windows 11 and compatible HID hardware.
